        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM EDT/530 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Beverly Shores, or near Michigan City, moving east
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Michigan City, Trail Creek, New Buffalo, Three Oaks, Long Beach,
Pottawattamie Park, Shorewood-Tower Hill, Shorewood-Tower
Hills-Harbert, Galien, Michiana Shores, Grand Beach, Michiana, Union
Pier, Glendora, Waterford, New Troy, Harbert, Sawyer, Lakeside In
Berrien County, and Hesston.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 48 and 61.
Interstate 94 in Indiana between mile markers 36 and 45.
Interstate 94 in Michigan between mile markers 0 and 12.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
